<mjml>
  <mj-head>
    <mj-style> h2,img,p { margin:0; } td{ padding-top:0 !important; } p {margin-bottom: 10px;}</mj-style>
    <mj-font name="Roboto" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Roboto" />
    <mj-font name="Roboto+Serif" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto  +Serif:ital,opsz,wght@0,8..144,100..900;1,8..144,100..900&display=swap" />
  </mj-head>
  <mj-body background-color="#f0f1f3"> 
    
    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
    <!-- Logo Header -->  
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-spacer height="10px" />
      <mj-column padding="10px 12px 10px 12px" width="100%">
        <mj-spacer height="16px" />
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" css-class="light_img" width="150px" src="https://www.geopolitics.world/gp-logo-grey.png" href="https://www.geopolitics.world" alt="" />
        
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 0px" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 2px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
            ">Did you know that the King of the UK receives daily updates on government affairs through a red dispatch box every morning?</p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
            "><strong>On 16th Dec 2024 edition:</strong> </p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              padding-left: 10px;
            ">→ South Korean president impeached</p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              padding-left: 10px;
            ">→ U.S. talks with HTS</p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              padding-left: 10px;
            ">→ What was the Berlin conference?</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 0px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-spacer height="10px"></mj-spacer>
    <!-- Spotlight -->
    <mj-section css-class="mj_fsection" background-color="#ffffff" css-class="mj_fsection">
      <mj-column background-color="#ffffff" width="100%">
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px 0px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="white">
          <h2 style="
          color:#06266D;
            text-align: left;
            letter-spacing:6px;
            border-bottom:2px solid #06266D;
            text-transform:uppercase;
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 300;
              padding: 18px 8px 10px 8px; 
              
            ">SPOTLIGHT</h2>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section> 
    <!-- Content sections -->
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">Bend it like Kavelashvili</h2>
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopolitics.world/email/images/gp-dec-16-1.jpg" alt="Bend it like Kavelashvili" href="https://www.geopolitics.world" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Georgian lawmakers have <a href="https://www.france24.com/en/europe/20241214-georgian-lawmakers-elect-far-right-ruling-party-loyalist-mikheil-kavelashvili-as-president" target="_blank">elected</a> Mikheil Kavelashvili, a far-right loyalist of the ruling Georgian Dream party and vocal critic of the West, as the country’s new president. The election follows protests over the government’s decision to halt Georgia’s EU accession talks until 2028 despite overwhelming public support for EU membership. Opposition parties have boycotted parliament since October, citing fraud in elections. Kavelashvili, the sole candidate for the role, is also a former <a href="https://talksport.com/football/2379755/man-city-mikheil-kavelashvili-president-georgia/" target="_blank">soccer player</a> and ally of ex-Prime Minister Bidzina Ivanishvili.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4; filter: blur(5px);">Protests against the <a href="https://www.cbsnews.com/news/georgia-protests-russia-european-union-nato-what-to-know/" target="_blank">government</a> continue in Tbilisi, the capital. Demonstrators blast the pro-Russian pivot and restrictions on dissent. Outgoing President <a href="https://www.euronews.com/my-europe/2024/12/15/georgias-president-slams-her-successors-appointment-as-a-mockery-of-democracy" target="_blank">Salome Zourabichvili</a>, part of the pro-EU opposition, has refused to recognize the election and has vowed to lead the protest movement. Opposition parties have claimed they will regard Zourabichvili as their president even after Kavelashvili’s inauguration on Dec. 29. Western nations have expressed concern over Georgia’s foreign policy pivot and authoritarian drift.​</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>


    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
  </mj-body>
</mjml>